cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as gendered pronoun resolution. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses BERT, a popular deep learning model, for the task. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves training neural networks, and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it uses contextual embeddings for the task.
